OL,3,CShopkeepers appeal to council after
OL,4,Crents are raised by over 100%
OL,6,FShe continued: "It was a great shock,
OL,7,FI couldn't stand up. How could I
OL,8,Fafford that first of all, and then how
OL,9,Fcan I pass these increases to my
OL,10,Fcustomers to cover that increase?"
OL,12,FCurrently, a small wash in the
OL,13,Flaunderette would cost #5 but
OL,14,Ffollowing the increase, she would have
OL,15,Fto nearly triple the price.
OL,17,F"I still cannot cover all the costs.
OL,18,FMy business isn't failing, but this
OL,19,Fincrease will consume a big portion of
OL,20,Fmy small profit. it means I'd be
OL,21,Fworking for nothing," she adds.
