OL,3,CShopkeepers appeal to council after
OL,4,Crents are raised by over 100%
OL,6,F"If that happens people will stop
OL,7,Fcoming to us, and travel further where
OL,8,Fthey sell cheaper and we will see a
OL,9,Fdecrease in customers, and therefore
OL,10,Four income and we will not survive -
OL,11,Fit's not sustainable.
OL,13,F"This is our business, we have nothing
OL,14,Felse for our livelihood."
OL,16,FMichelle Simpson has owned a
OL,17,Fhairdressers in the area for 12 years
OL,18,Fand says the area was a reason for
OL,19,Fopening her business.
